an><span style=\"font-weight:bold;color:rgb(175,0,255)\">in</span><span style=\"color:rgb(188,188,188)\"> </span>world_xyz)<span style=\"font-weight:bold;color:rgb(175,95,135)\">}</span><span style=\"color:rgb(175,0,0)\"> mm maps to voxel </span><span style=\"color:rgb(175,0,0)\">\"</span>\n<span class=\"ansi-green-fg ansi-bold\">    258</span>         <span style=\"color:rgb(175,0,0)\">f</span><span style=\"color:rgb(175,0,0)\">\"</span><span style=\"font-weight:bold;color:rgb(175,95,135)\">{</span><span style=\"color:rgb(0,135,0)\">tuple</span>(<span style=\"color:rgb(0,135,0)\">int</span>(v)<span style=\"color:rgb(188,188,188)\"> </span><span style=\"font-weight:bold;color:rgb(0,135,0)\">for</span><span style=\"color:rgb(188,188,188)\"> </span>v<span style=\"color:rgb(188,188,188)\"> </span><span style=\"font-weight:bold;color:rgb(175,0,255)\">in</span><span style=\"color:rgb(188,188,188)\"> </span>voxel)<span style=\"font-weight:bold;color:rgb(175,95,135)\">}</span><span style=\"color:rgb(175,0,0)\"> which is outside the image grid </span><span style=\"color:rgb(175,0,0)\">\"</span>\n<span class=\"ansi-green-fg ansi-bold\">    259</span>         <span style=\"color:rgb(175,0,0)\">f</span><span style=\"color:rgb(175,0,0)\">\"</span><span style=\"color:rgb(175,0,0)\">of shape </span><span style=\"font-weight:bold;color:rgb(175,95,135)\">{</span><span style=\"color:rgb(0,135,0)\">self</span><span style=\"color:rgb(98,98,98)\">.</span>_spatial_shape()<span style=\"font-weight:bold;color:rgb(175,95,135)\">}</span><span style=\"color:rgb(175,0,0)\">.</span><span style=\"color:rgb(175,0,0)\">\"</span>\n<span class=\"ansi-green-fg ansi-bold\">    260</span>     )\n\n<span class=\"ansi-red-fg\">ValueError</span>: world coord (9999.0, 9999.0, 9999.0) mm maps to voxel (5004, 5004, 4002) which is outside the image grid of shape (8, 8, 4).</pre>\n```\n:::\n\n:::\n:::\n\n\nAn off-grid world coordinate raises `ValueError`:\n`world coord (…) mm maps to voxel (…) which is outside the image grid\nof shape (…).` — *before* signed indexing can return a value from the\nopposite corner. The `out_of_bounds=\"zero\"` opt-in exists for\nalgorithms that intentionally want zero-fill; the default is `\"raise\"`.\nBacked by [scenario S01](https://github.com/bbuchsbaum/neuroim-python/blob/main/examples/scenarios/01_mni_spotlight/REPORT.md).\n\n## See also\n\n- [Start 03 — ROI extraction](../start/03-roi.qmd)\n- [Concept: Contract failures](../concepts/contract-failures.qmd) — the `WORLD-OOB` refusal.\n- [Spec: contract-failure vocabulary](../spec/contract-failure-vocabulary.html)\n\n",
